The paper proposes a novel end-to-end approach for unsupervised clustering using deep learning techniques. The approach is evaluated on various datasets including text and image datasets, indicating the relevance to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of a differentiable loss function and optimization of normalized cuts suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the use of deep learning models for clustering suggests a possible relevance to neural networks (cs.NE).
